How Claude project knowledge works:
Every document you upload to the project folder is automatically available to every new chat in this project. Claude searches the project knowledge at the start of every conversation. So:
Documents in project folder:
✅ WDP-ARCHITECTURE.md
✅ WDP-COMPONENTS.md  
✅ WDP-HANDOVER.md
✅ WDP-DECISIONS.md
✅ WDP-INTEGRATIONS.md
✅ WDP-NFRS.md

All of these are available to EVERY
new chat automatically — you don't
need to paste or upload them again.
So the answer is:
No — you don't need to paste the handover document each time.
You just need to say at the start of each new chat:
"You are my senior architecture partner
for WDP. We are continuing to fill
WDP-COMPONENTS.md using Copilot CLI.
Next component is [component name].
Here is the Copilot output:"
[paste Copilot response]
Claude will automatically read WDP-HANDOVER.md and WDP-COMPONENTS.md from the project knowledge and know exactly where you are.
The one thing you DO need to do between sessions:
When you finish a component in one chat
↓
Update that section in WDP-COMPONENTS.md
(change 📝 DRAFT to ✅ COMPLETE,
fill in the confirmed content)
↓
Re-upload the updated WDP-COMPONENTS.md
to the project folder
↓
Next chat automatically sees the
updated version with progress saved
That's the only maintenance step — keep WDP-COMPONENTS.md updated in the project folder as you complete each component. Everything else is automatic.